{"questionId":"9085097","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the work done to bring a small charge <em>q</em> from infinity to point C.</p>\n<p>Data given:</p>\n<p><em>Q</em> = 2.0 × 10<sup>−3</sup> C,</p>\n<p><em>q</em> = 4.0 × 10<sup>−9</sup> C</p>\n<p><em>D</em> = 1.2 m</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>V</em> «= 2 × <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>9</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>60</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>» = 6.0 × 10<sup>7</sup> «V» ✓</p>\n<p><em>W</em> = «qV = 6.0 × 10<sup>7</sup> × 4.0 × 10<sup>−9</sup> =» 0.24 «J» ✓</p>\n<p><em>Allow <strong>ECF</strong> from <strong>MP1</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9085097","referenceCode":"23M.2.HL.TZ1.ii","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Calculate the work done to bring a small charge q from infinity to point C. Data given: Q = 2.0 × 10−3 C, q = 4.0 × 10−9 C D = 1.2 m","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D.2 Electric and magnetic fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}